Inputs\: keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable. Returns\: The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable. Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value. notNull - if some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned. 746638cf-b43c-433d-bac3-4c86511d41f9.1cc3f400-83c6-4d17-bbdd-9149ef9ed3cd.description=

Inputs\:

This is an operation that does nothing, and can be used to display information to the user by editing the display tab. It can also be used for filtering flow variables by feeding them in as inputs, and filtering them on the results tab.

Inputs\:
field1 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field2 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field3 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field4 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Responses\:
success - this operation never fails.

trapSourceIp - TrapSourceIp  from the ASP search
siteId - SiteId  from the ASP search
objectId - ObjectId  from the ASP search
aspId - ASP Id  from the ASP search
EventId - Event Id from the event
TrapSourceIp - TrapSourceIp from the event
SiteId - SiteId from the event
ObjectId - ObjectId from the event

Outputs\:
aspId - ASP Id

Responses\:
success - If everything went fine.
failure - If something went wrong.
